# Cloudflare Pages headers
# ES modules + CSS are cached by URL; filenames don't change between
# deploys, so browsers reuse stale copies and a deploy looks half-applied
# (e.g. desktop updated, phone still on the old bundle). `no-cache` keeps
# the file but forces a revalidation each load: unchanged files return a
# cheap 304, changed files download fresh. No more stuck-stale visitors.
/*
  Cache-Control: no-cache
